snippet: Officers were called to the Manhattan home of the baby’s parents twice before, the police said.
abstract: New York City detectives question parents of 4-month-old Eduardo Rocha Ovalle, who died after he was taken to Manhattan hospital unconscious and with signs of bruising on his hands, feet and back; investigators spoke with child's father, Eduardo Rocha Bracamontes, and the mother, whose identity has not been released.
lead_paragraph: Officers were called to the Manhattan home of the baby’s parents twice before, the police said.

headline.main: Police Question Parents in Baby’s Death
headline.print_headline: Police Question Parents in Baby’s Death
